President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his Administration. 

1. Mary Toman of California is nominated to be the Under Secretary of Commerce for Economic Affairs. She has previously served as a member of the Department of Transportation Advisory Committee on Human Trafficking and as the Deputy Treasurer of California. Toman has a B.A. in Economics from Stanford University and an M.B.A from Harvard Business School.

2. Michael Nemelka of Utah is nominated to be a Deputy United States Trade Representative with the Rank of Ambassador. He currently serves as a Special Advisor to Ambassador Robert E. Lighthizer, the United States Trade Representative. Nemelka has a background in complex commercial litigation and holds a B.A. in History from Brigham Young University and a J.D. from the University of Virginia School of Law.

3. Katharine T. Sullivan of Colorado is nominated to be an Assistant Attorney General for the Office of Justice Programs. She currently serves as the Principal Deputy Assistant Attorney General for the Office of Justice Programs at the Department of Justice. Sullivan has experience as a Judge in the 5th Judicial District of Colorado and as a Deputy District Attorney. She earned her B.A from Syracuse University and her J.D from George Washington University Law School.